<div class="description-box">
<div class="description-title">Fuji 5 Lakes Ultramarathon 100km</div>
<div>
2018-04-22 <img src="https://media.istockphoto.com/id/1442152045/vector/path-route-icon-distance-symbol.jpg?s=612x612&w=0&k=20&c=2ilIa1pWHJp550B31t__1NPc0CHpouutgdxt7QO4EJg=" class="static-icon">96 km <img src="https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcS_EkMEkMAdgDcE0W6nELzmmMrqHToRcoS8eA&s" class="static-icon">1607 m <img src="https://cdn-icons-png.freepik.com/512/13063/13063145.png" class="static-icon"><span>11:29:02</span>
        <a href="https://www.strava.com/activities/1523885936" class="icon-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><img src="https://cdn.worldvectorlogo.com/logos/strava-2.svg" class="icon"></a></div>

<br>

<div class="description-text">Never been in this much pain before, but I made it.

It was way steeper than I expected, probably should have checked that altitude map more in detail, or not.

Everything started to hurt after 40km.

Cried a bit after finishing

Official result was 11:28 I think, that includes all the stops and walking, especially during those last kilometers where someone put an unnecessarily steep mountain.</div>

